  <mainDescription>&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Description&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defect prevention focuses on reducing the number of defects injected during software development. Teams&#xD;
    must&amp;nbsp;identify defects quickly in order to minimize their impact.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Symptoms&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Symptoms that indicate the need to increase defect prevention include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        High pre-shipment and post-shipment defect reports&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Growing defect backlog&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solutions&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following solutions help to increase the ability to prevent defects from occurring:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    High Impact:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/effective_scm_solution_CEAA41E4.html&quot; guid=&quot;_81GxwLRZEd6qwtTa3nKvcw&quot;>Effective SCM Solution&lt;/a> - Effectively control change by implementing software&#xD;
        configuration management solutions.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/improve_developer_effectiveness_1089DC4C.html&quot; guid=&quot;_0MmLMLbHEd6_i8GY7ieNyA&quot;>Improve Developer Effectiveness&lt;/a> - Reduce manual work by developers by&#xD;
        leveraging existing patterns and automated tools to transform model to model or model to code.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/rearchitect_for_reuse_503CC74C.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Gc7bsMyEEd6AlLazTePGRg&quot;>Re-Architect for Reuse&lt;/a> - Re-architect existing solutions to improve reusability&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Medium Impact:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/effectively_elicit_requirments_8BF5A812.html&quot; guid=&quot;_3dwIALRYEd6qwtTa3nKvcw&quot;>Effectively Elicit Requirements&lt;/a> - Effectively communicate with stakeholders to&#xD;
        understand the right requirements and capabilities throughout the project.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/effectively_manage_rqmts_monitor_scope_D8751333.html&quot; guid=&quot;_CEDYULRZEd6qwtTa3nKvcw&quot;>Effectively Manage Requirements and Monitor Scope&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;- Manage stakeholders'&#xD;
        expectations and communicate the value of the selected scope.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/improve_lifecycle_collaboration_31E3F561.html&quot; guid=&quot;_R3YuMLRZEd6qwtTa3nKvcw&quot;>Improve Lifecycle Collaboration&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;- Improve collaboration by providing&#xD;
        lifecycle integration across otherwise disconnected team members.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Low Impact:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/architect_and_communicate_soln_4B3FC0DE.html&quot; guid=&quot;_xf5XkLRaEd6qwtTa3nKvcw&quot;>Architect and Communicate the Solution&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp; - Develop the architecture and&#xD;
        communicate the solution to the team.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
